{"accepted":[{"assertion":"Formal-Conjectures statement: FC 102 (PR #3422) [in-pr] https://github.com/google-deepmind/formal-conjectures/pull/3422.","id":"vf_e14be79608b379f1","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"Erdős Problem #102: declared status 'open'. Formalized: no. Let $c>0$ and $h_c(n)$ be such that for any $n$ points in $\\mathbb{R}^2$ such that there are $\\geq cn^2$ lines each containing more than three points, there must be some line containing $h_c(n)$ many points. Estimate $h_c(n)$. Is it true that, for fixed $c>0$, we have $h_c(n)\\to \\infty$? Current best: It is easy to see that $h_c(n) \\ll_c n^{1/2}$, and Erd\\H{o}s at one point \\cite{Er95} suggested that perhaps a similar lower bound $h_c(n)\\gg_c n^{1/2}$ holds. Prize: no. Tags: geometry.","id":"vf_ea9de85dbae7be5d","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"}],"accepted_activity":false,"activity":[],"activity_types":[],"attempt_count":0,"banked_attempt_count":0,"commits":[],"dependency_impact":"none","detail_url":"problems/102.json","draft_proposals":[],"edges":[{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_e14be79608b379f1","source_root":"sha256:d3db36661e28b7570fc8704bf8455b80d8382beded47d069f2c386144d90a238","target":"erdos:102","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Materialized typed link between accepted findings.","inferred":true,"relation":"synthesized_from","source":"vf_e14be79608b379f1","source_root":"sha256:d3db36661e28b7570fc8704bf8455b80d8382beded47d069f2c386144d90a238","target":"vf_ea9de85dbae7be5d","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_ea9de85dbae7be5d","source_root":"sha256:d3db36661e28b7570fc8704bf8455b80d8382beded47d069f2c386144d90a238","target":"erdos:102","trust":"signed"}],"external_references":[],"formal_conjectures_activity":null,"frontier_id":"vfr_0a25edab